<p><strong>Ayurveda</strong></p>

<p>Dosha balance is emphasized, and suppressing natural urges is considered unhealthy and claimed to lead to illness. Ayurveda treatises describe three elemental doshas viz. vƒÅta, pitta and kapha, and state that balance (Skt. sƒÅmyatva) of the doshas results in health, while imbalance (vi·π£amatva) results in disease. Ayurveda treatises divide medicine into eight canonical components.</p>

