<p><strong>Chinese Medicine</strong></p>

<p>One of the basic tenets is that the body‚Äôs vital energy (ch‚Äôi or qi) is circulating through channels called meridians having branches connected to bodily organs and functions.The concept of vital energy is pseudoscientific. Concepts of the body and of disease used in TCM reflect its ancient origins and its emphasis on dynamic processes over material structure, similar to the humoral theory of ancient Greece and ancient Rome.</p>

